attributes.magic: ELF 32-bit LSB executable, ARM, EABI4 version 1 (SYSV), statically linked, stripped

threat_severity.level_description: Severity HIGH because it was considered trojan. Other contributing factor was that it could not be run in sandboxes.

crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: This sample is a statically linked ARMv7 botnet, likely a variant of the Mirai or Mozi families, targeting IoT devices. It contains a massive embedded credential list for brute-forcing services (function sub_1534c) and a downloader module that uses wget, curl, and tftp to fetch and execute malicious shell scripts (sub_15088). The binary includes extensive process-scanning capabilities, iterating through /proc to identify and terminate competing processes such as telnetd, sshd, and login (sub_12e0c, sub_11f84). It also features advanced networking routines, including the use of DNS-over-HTTPS (DoH) for stealthy command-and-control resolution (sub_10d48).
